ReasonableCauseExplanation.ExplanationTxt: THE FOUNDATION IS RESPECTFULLY REQUESTING ABATEMENT OF ALL PENALTIES FOR THE 2020 FORM 990-PF AND 990-T DUE TO THE FOLLOWING. THE FOUNDATION ENGAGED A DULY QUALIFIED CPA FIRM TO HANDLE THE FORM 990-PF AND FORM 990-T FILINGS. THIS CPA FIRM HAS COMPLETED ALL THE FOUNDATION'S TAX FILINGS FROM THE INITIAL 2012 TAX YEAR TO THE PRESENT. THE CPA FIRM PROPERLY FILED AN AUTOMATIC SIX-MONTH EXTENSION OF TIME TO FILE THE 2020 TAX RETURNS, WHICH EXTENDED THE DUE DATE TO NOVEMBER 15, 2021. THE FOUNDATION ROUTINELY APPLIES FOR AN EXTENSION DUE TO SEVERAL INVESTMENT SCHEDULE K-1S THAT ARE NOT RECEIVED UNTIL THE FALL, AFTER THE ORIGINAL DUE DATE. THE PARTNER RESPONSIBLE FOR ENSURING THE FORM 990-PF AND FORM 990-T WERE TIMELY FILED WAS OUT ON MEDICAL LEAVE FOR SEVERAL MONTHS DURING 2021, AND THE E-FILING WAS MISSED INTERNALLY BY THE PARTNER'S TEAM. THE RETURNS HAD BEEN PREPARED AND REVIEWED, BUT THE SERVICE TEAM FAILED TO PROPERLY EXPORT AND FILE E-FILE THE RETURNS WITH THE SERVICE. THIS WAS AN HONEST MISTAKE ON BEHALF OF THE CPA FIRM DUE TO THE PARTNER BEING OUT FOR SEVERAL MONTHS. TO ENSURE THIS NEVER HAPPENS AGAIN, THE CPA FIRM HAS NOW ADDED AN ADDITIONAL STEP IN WORKFLOW REVIEW. ITS RETURN TRACKING DUE DATE REPORT IS NOW DISTRIBUTED TO ALL TAX PARTNERS IN THE FIRM SO THAT MORE PEOPLE ARE AWARE OF SCHEDULED DEADLINES. FURTHER, AN ADDITIONAL REVIEW OF E-FILE ACCEPTANCE AND CONFIRMATION WAS ADDED TO THE PROFESSIONAL SUPPORT TEAM'S REQUIREMENTS ON ALL RETURN FILINGS. THE FOUNDATION RELIES ON THE CPA FIRM TO ENSURE ALL ITS FILINGS ARE COMPLETED PROPERLY AND TIMELY. THE FOUNDATION PROVIDED ALL INFORMATION TIMELY TO THE CPA FIRM TO COMPLETE THE 2020 FILING.DURING THE CPA FIRM'S INTERNAL REVIEW OF ALL 2020 FILINGS BEFORE TAX YEAR 2020 E-FILING WENT DOWN, IT WAS DISCOVERED THAT THE FORM 990-PF AND FORM 990-T FOR THE FOUNDATION HAD BEEN PREPARED AND REVIEWED BUT NOT ELECTRONICALLY FILED. THE CPA FIRM IMMEDIATELY E-FILED THE RETURNS. THE FOUNDATION OPERATED IN GOOD FAITH AND DID NOT DISPLAY INTENTIONAL DISREGARD OF THE FILING DEADLINES. FURTHER, THE FOUNDATION HAS A GOOD HISTORY OF TIMELY FILING THEIR FORM 990-PF AND FORM 990-T. FOR THESE REASONS, WE RESPECTFULLY REQUEST AN ABATEMENT OF ANY PENALTIES THAT MAY ARISE.
